Albert Bontridder (born April 4, 1921 in Anderlecht) is a Belgian architect and writer. In 1953 he married Olga Dohnalova, a Czech refugee, and together they had two children.
He graduated as an architect in 1942. As an architect, he made the plan for the house of his friend Louis Paul Boon. He was an editor of the experimental illustrated magazines Tijd en Mens (E: Time and Man) (19491955) and Kentering (E: Change) (19661977). He published his first poems he in French and he made his actual debut with Hoog water (E: high tide) (1951).

